title: Grain mostly higher and livestock higher
text:
Tip : Use comma (,) to separate multiple quotes. Learn more... 
Thu, Aug 13, 2015, 21:03 BST - UK Markets closed Grain mostly higher and livestock higher Wheat, corn and soybeans higher and oats lower on the CBOT; beef and pork higher on the CME. Associated Press – 24 minutes ago Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly higher Thursday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was up 11 cents to $5.0325 a bushel; December corn rose 7.25 cents to 3.7525 a bushel; December oats fell .25 cents to 2.3950 a bushel; while November soybeans advanced 17 cents to $9.27 a bushel. 
Beef and pork were higher on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was up 1.25 cents to $1.4785 a pound; August feeder cattle rose .15 cent to $2.1402 a pound; while October lean hogs gained 1.68 cents to $.6505 a pound.
